[{"id":"publishers/ccdd-gate.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# ccdd-gate\n\nThe CCDD gate tooling knowledge - how the deterministic verification gate works and integrates.\n\n## Consume\n\nProject page (origin-collapse applies) - consume locally:\n\n```\ngit clone -b gh-pages https://github.com/MauricioPerera/ccdd-gate\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm --serve ./ccdd-gate\n```\n\n## Topics\n\nCCDD gate, linting, complexity measurement, integration gates.","okf_concept":"publishers/ccdd-gate.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"ccdd-gate"}},{"id":"publishers/ccdd.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# ccdd\n\nSpecs, workflow and findings of the CCDD methodology - deterministic gates R1-R9 for AI-implemented code.\n\n## Consume\n\nProject page (origin-collapse applies) - consume locally:\n\n```\ngit clone -b gh-pages https://github.com/MauricioPerera/ccdd\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm --serve ./ccdd\n```\n\n## Topics\n\nCCDD methodology, deterministic verification gates, task contracts.","okf_concept":"publishers/ccdd.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"CCDD (Complexity-Controlled Development)"}},{"id":"publishers/game-protocol.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# game-protocol\n\nAn interaction protocol spec published in-source - its Pages serves the repo root, so the publisher lives inside the source tree.\n\n## Consume\n\nProject page (origin-collapse applies) - consume locally:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/MauricioPerera/game-protocol\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm --serve ./game-protocol\n```\n\n## Topics\n\nGame/interaction protocol, in-source publishing.","okf_concept":"publishers/game-protocol.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"game-protocol"}},{"id":"publishers/kdd.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# KDD\n\nKnowledge Driven Development: a methodology where project knowledge lives as\nan OKF bundle and drives contracts and validation. Its 40 concepts are\npublished as a searchable, hash-pinned knowledge base.\n\n## Consume\n\nDirectly from the root origin (aggregated under the `kdd` scope):\n\n```\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm https://mauricioperera.github.io\n# -> kdd__search_knowledge, kdd__list_concepts\n```\n\nOr locally with the full bundle (includes get_concept):\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/MauricioPerera/KDD\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm --serve ./KDD\n```\n\n## Topics\n\nKDD methodology, OKF contracts, project initialization, validation.","okf_concept":"publishers/kdd.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"KDD (Knowledge Driven Development)"}},{"id":"publishers/llms-txt-skills.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# llms-txt-skills\n\nThe standard dogfoods itself: its GitHub Pages publishes a 6-concept OKF\nbundle (what the standard is, adoption ladder L0-L3, trust model, executable\nskills, publishing, consuming) with `search_knowledge`/`get_concept`/\n`list_concepts`, a custom `validate_skill_line` skill, a demo-signed index,\nand signed knowledge-freshness attestations gated in CI.\n\n## Consume\n\nProject page (origin-collapse applies): consume via the root origin — its\nskills are aggregated there — or locally:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/MauricioPerera/llms-txt-skills\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm --serve ./llms-txt-skills/docs\n```\n\n## Topics\n\nThe llms.txt Skills standard, RFC v0.10, extensions v0.5/v0.4, freshness.","okf_concept":"publishers/llms-txt-skills.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"llms-txt-skills (the standard itself)"}},{"id":"publishers/llmstxt-demo-site.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# llmstxt-demo-site.rckflr.workers.dev\n\nThe first live publisher of the ecosystem and the gateway's field-test\ntarget: `sum_numbers`, `server_time` (uses `host.fetchOrigin`), and the\nwrite-skill demo (`create_payment`/`refund_payment` against a real D1\ndatabase) exercised by mcpwasm's production-integration CI job.\n\n## Consume\n\n```\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm https://llmstxt-demo-site.rckflr.workers.dev\n```\n\n## Topics\n\nDemo skills, sandboxed execution, origin-scoped fetch, write operations.","okf_concept":"publishers/llmstxt-demo-site.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"llmstxt-demo-site (Workers demo)"}},{"id":"publishers/mauricioperera-github-io.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# mauricioperera.github.io\n\nThe reference multi-project origin of the ecosystem, and the best first stop:\none `llms.txt` serves `site_facts`, the standard's own skills\n(`validate_skill_line`, `search_knowledge`, `list_concepts`) and the KDD\nmethodology bundle namespaced as `kdd__search_knowledge` /\n`kdd__list_concepts` — each scope bound to its own hash-verified BM25 memory\n(Executable Skills v0.5 §2.5).\n\n## Consume\n\n```\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm https://mauricioperera.github.io\n```\n\nAlso works in the browser (mcpwasm-web) — the origin serves CORS.\n\n## Topics\n\nllms.txt skills standard, adoption, trust model, executable skills, origin\nmemory, KDD (Knowledge Driven Development) concepts.","okf_concept":"publishers/mauricioperera-github-io.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"mauricioperera.github.io (root, multi-project)"}},{"id":"publishers/taskmd.md#0","metadata":{"content":"# taskmd\n\nTask management as markdown - the taskmd format and workflow published as searchable knowledge.\n\n## Consume\n\nProject page (origin-collapse applies) - consume locally:\n\n```\ngit clone -b gh-pages https://github.com/MauricioPerera/taskmd\nnpx -y @rckflr/mcpwasm --serve ./taskmd\n```\n\n## Topics\n\nTask management, markdown workflows.","okf_concept":"publishers/taskmd.md","okf_type":"Publisher","title":"taskmd"}}]